.TH COMMAND * 2014-04-08 "SequoiaDB" "Sequoiadb sdb's Manual"
.ad l.ll 72.ce 1000
\fBcursor.hint()\fR
.ce 0
.sp 2

.SH "NAME"

.sp 2
hint - Visit result set using specified index.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.sp 2

.sp 2

.sp 2
cousor.hint(\fB[hint]\fR)
.SH "CATEGORY"

.sp 2

.sp 2
Cursor
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

.sp 2
Visit result set using specified index.
.sp 2
\fBhint (json object)\fR
.br
       It specifies the visiting plan to accelarate query speed.
.sp 2
       \fBFormat\fR
.br
              The method "cursor.hint()" contains parameter
              "hint". If it is not specified, the query will not
              use index to visit records. The parameter "hint"
              contain a one-field json object. The field name is
              ignored. But the field value is specified as the
              index which will be visited. When it is null, it
              will visit all the records in the collection.
.br
              {"":null} or {"":"<indexname>"}
.SH "Examples"

.sp 2
Find records that contains the field "age" in the collection
"bar" using the index "ageIndex" and return results.
.sp 2
db.foo.bar.find({age:{$exists:1}}).hint({"":"ageIndex"})